---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms & Conditions - Hack-Nocturne '25"
  description="Terms and conditions for Hack-Nocturne '25 hackathon platform and participation."
>
  <Header showMenu={false} showBackLink={true} />
  
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <header class="legal-header">
          <h1>Terms & Conditions</h1>
          <div class="legal-meta">
            <span><strong>Effective Date:</strong> July 27, 2025</span>
            <span><strong>Governing Law & Venue:</strong> Laws of India; courts of Bengaluru</span>
          </div>
        </header>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>These Terms & Conditions ("T&C") govern your access to and use of the Hack-Nocturne hackathon organizing platform (the "Platform"), owned and operated by TechHub & GLUG MVIT. By registering or using the Platform, you agree to comply with these T&C.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
          <p>Users must be at least 18 years old and residents of India. Minors are not permitted to register or use the Platform.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>3. User Accounts</h2>
          <div class="legal-subsection">
            <p><strong>3.1.</strong> Registration requires name, email, phone number, GitHub project link, and team information.</p>
            <p><strong>3.2.</strong> You are solely responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activities under your account.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>4. Platform Services</h2>
          <div class="legal-subsection">
            <p><strong>4.1. Participants:</strong> access hackathon details, submit projects, view checkpoints, receive system messages, and communicate with organizers.</p>
            <p><strong>4.2. Organizers:</strong> manage participants and teams, can export data (JSON/CSV), send broadcasts, configure check-in, timer, leaderboards, rubrics, provide/review Participant's GitHub, surveys and can upload or manage media.</p>
            <p><strong>4.3. Jury:</strong> scan QR codes or search participants, review and judge projects, assign scores, and add notes.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>5. Data Collection & Use</h2>
          <div class="legal-subsection">
            <p><strong>5.1. Personal Data:</strong> name, email, phone, team details, GitHub link, IP address, analytics, and Devfolio-sourced participant data.</p>
            <p><strong>5.2. Usage Data:</strong> basic site analytics via Cloudflare.</p>
            <p><strong>5.3. Sharing:</strong> with sponsors/partners for internships or prizes; jury access limited to basic participant data and revoked one week post-event.</p>
            <p><strong>5.4. Retention:</strong> data retained up to two years post-event. Erasure requests honored only after six months have elapsed; requests made via <a href="mailto:legal@hack-nocturne.in?subject=Data+Erasure+Request+-+Hack-Nocturne">legal@hack-nocturne.in</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>6. Payments</h2>
          <div class="legal-subsection">
            <p><strong>6.1.</strong> Accommodation, food, and ancillary service fees processed via Razorpay.</p>
            <p><strong>6.2.</strong> All payment disputes or refunds handled according to Razorpay's policies.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <div class="legal-subsection">
            <p><strong>7.1.</strong> Participants retain full ownership of projects created during the hackathon.</p>
            <p><strong>7.2.</strong> Organizers receive an exclusive, two-year, royalty-free license to promote and showcase submissions, provided original creators and team names are credited.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>8. Code of Conduct</h2>
          <p>The Platform adopts the <a href="https://devfolio.co/code-of-conduct" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Devfolio Code of Conduct</a>. Any violation may result in immediate suspension.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>9. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>The Platform integrates services from Cloudflare, NeonDB, Zoho ZeptoMail, Grafana Cloud, AWS/EC2, R2, Azure, GCP, Razorpay, and Google Maps. Each service operates under its own terms and privacy policies, over which TechHub & GLUG MVIT has no control.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>10. Communication Preferences</h2>
          <p>Marketing emails only sent to users who have explicitly opted in; no automated/targeted SMS or WhatsApp communications.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>11. Prizes, Internships, & Liability</h2>
          <div class="legal-subsection">
            <p><strong>11.1.</strong> The Platform and organizers may facilitate prize distribution and internship offers.</p>
            <p><strong>11.2. Limitation of Liability:</strong> TechHub & GLUG MVIT is not liable for delays, damages, or failures related to prizes or third-party offers. Participation and prize fulfilment are at the sole risk of the user.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>12. Suspension & Termination</h2>
          <p>TechHub & GLUG MVIT reserves the right to suspend or terminate access for any policy violation without prior notice.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
          <h2>13. Amendments</h2>
          <p>We may amend these T&C at any time. Registered users will receive seven days' advance notice from <a href="mailto:legal@hack-nocturne.in">legal@hack-nocturne.in</a>. Continued use after effective date constitutes acceptance.</p>
        </section>

        <footer class="legal-footer">
          <div class="contact-info">
            <h3>Contact Information</h3>
            <span>For questions regarding these Terms & Conditions, please contact us at:</span>
            <span><a href="mailto:legal@hack-nocturne.in">legal@hack-nocturne.in</a></span>
          </div>
          <div class="last-updated">
            <em>Last updated: July 27, 2025</em>
          </div>
        </footer>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer hideMargin />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: var(--color-bg-primary);
    padding: var(--space-20) 0 var(--space-16);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-6);
  }

  .legal-content {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-frosted-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-2xl);
    padding: var(--space-12);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-2xl);
    backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
  }

  .legal-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-frosted-border);
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  }

  .legal-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .legal-meta span {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: var(--font-size-md);
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    scroll-margin-top: var(--space-20);
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    line-height: var(--line-height-snug);
  }

  .legal-section p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--font-size-md);
  }

  .legal-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-subsection {
    background: var(--color-bg-tertiary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-frosted-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .legal-subsection p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .legal-subsection p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-footer {
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--color-frosted-border);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .contact-info {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .contact-info h3 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .contact-info p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  }

  /* Links */
  a {
    color: var(--color-text-link);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  }

  a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  a:focus {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-primary);
    outline-offset: 2px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  /* Strong/Bold text styling */
  strong {
    color: var(--color-white);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  }

  /* Responsive Design */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-page {
      padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-12);
    }

    .container {
      padding: 0 var(--space-4);
    }

    .legal-content {
      padding: var(--space-8);
    }

    .legal-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    }

    .legal-meta {
      text-align: left;
    }

    .legal-section h2 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    }

    .legal-section p {
      font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    }

    .legal-subsection {
      padding: var(--space-4);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .legal-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    }

    .legal-section h2 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
      border-left-width: 3px;
      padding-left: var(--space-3);
    }
  }

  /* Accessibility improvements */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    * {
      transition: none !important;
      animation: none !important;
    }
  }

  /* Print styles */
  @media print {
    .legal-page {
      background: white;
      color: black;
    }

    .legal-content {
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      box-shadow: none;
    }

    .legal-header h1,
    .legal-section h2,
    .legal-section h3,
    strong {
      color: black;
    }

    .legal-section p,
    .contact-info p,
    .legal-meta p {
      color: black;
    }

    a {
      color: blue;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  }
</style>
